# Reserved for business-logic services (orchestration layer).
#
# Services coordinate repositories and external systems (R2, Queues, Lark).
# Routes call services; services call repositories.
#
# Suggested modules (Phase 2+):
# - auth.service.ts        → login, register, password hashing
# - patient.service.ts     → patient CRUD, medical alerts
# - visit.service.ts       → visit lifecycle, status transitions
# - finding.service.ts     → clinical findings by tooth (FDI validation)
# - plan.service.ts        → treatment plan creation, approval, total recalc
# - payment.service.ts     → payment recording, outstanding balance
# - pdf.service.ts         → generate proposal PDF via pdf-lib
# - lark.service.ts        → create Lark task / calendar event from clinical data
#   (Architecture rule #7: Lark receives ONLY operational fields —
#    patient name OK, but no diagnosis details.)